---
const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'Is Rebound really free?',
    a: 'Yes. Rebound is free and open source under the MIT license. Every tool is included, with no account, no telemetry, and no trial clock. Use it for anything, personal or paid client work alike.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Is it open source?',
    a: 'Yes, under the MIT license. The full source is on GitHub at github.com/meszmate/rebound. Clone it, read it, build it yourself, or open a pull request. It is an original implementation built on public techniques like CSS cubic-bezier timing, the Penner equations and spring physics.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Where do I get it?',
    a: 'Download the .zxp for your operating system (there is a macOS build and a Windows build) from the GitHub Releases page, and install it with any ZXP installer like the free ZXPInstaller. Pick the file that matches your OS: a ZXP signed on the other platform installs but shows a blank panel. You can also clone the repository and build it from source. Both are covered in the README.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Which versions of After Effects does it support?',
    a: 'After Effects 2019 (16.0) and newer, on macOS and Windows. Rebound is a CEP extension. A few import details use newer AE APIs (per-run text styling needs AE 24.3 or newer) and degrade gracefully on older builds.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Does anything leave my machine?',
    a: 'No. There is no account and no telemetry. The Figma, Illustrator and Photoshop bridge runs over a local loopback receiver on your machine, or through a plain .rbir file on disk. Nothing is uploaded anywhere.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How does the import actually work?',
    a: 'The Figma plugin sends your selection to the panel over a local receiver while After Effects is open; the Illustrator and Photoshop exporters run from File ▸ Scripts. Every path produces the same portable .rbir document, rebuilds your design as native editable layers, and ends with a fidelity report of what transferred.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What happens with fonts?',
    a: 'Text imports as real, editable After Effects text. If a font is not installed, the import report flags it and offers a one-click replacement. Nothing substitutes silently.',
  },
];
---

<section id="faq" class="scroll-mt-20 border-t border-line-soft py-24 sm:py-32">
  <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-6xl gap-x-16 gap-y-10 px-5 sm:px-8 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_1.9fr]">
    <div class="lg:sticky lg:top-24 lg:self-start">
      <p class="text-sm font-medium text-live" data-reveal>FAQ</p>
      <h2
        class="mt-3 text-balance text-3xl font-semibold tracking-[-0.03em] text-ink sm:text-[2.5rem] sm:leading-[1.1]"
        data-reveal
        style="--reveal-delay: 0.06s"
      >
        Common questions.
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[0.9375rem] text-mute" data-reveal style="--reveal-delay: 0.12s">
        Something else? Ask in the&#32;<a
          href="https://github.com/meszmate/rebound/issues"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="text-ink underline decoration-line underline-offset-4 transition-colors hover:decoration-ink"
          >GitHub issues</a
        >.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      {
        faqs.map((f, i) => (
          <details
            class="rb-faq group border-t border-line-soft last:border-b"
            data-reveal
            style={`--reveal-delay: ${Math.min(i * 0.04, 0.2)}s`}
          >
            <summary class="flex cursor-pointer list-none items-center justify-between gap-4 py-5 text-[1.0625rem] font-medium tracking-[-0.01em] text-ink transition-colors hover:text-ink-soft">
              {f.q}
              <span class="rb-faq-icon grid h-7 w-7 shrink-0 place-items-center rounded-full border border-line text-mute transition-colors group-hover:border-[rgb(16_17_20/0.2)]">
                <svg viewBox="0 0 12 12" class="h-3 w-3" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
                  <path d="M6 1.5v9M1.5 6h9" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round" />
                </svg>
              </span>
            </summary>
            <p class="max-w-2xl pb-6 text-[0.9375rem] leading-relaxed text-mute">{f.a}</p>
          </details>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  /* Animate <details> open/close where supported (Chromium 131+); harmless elsewhere. */
  :global(html) {
    interpolate-size: allow-keywords;
  }
  details.rb-faq::details-content {
    opacity: 0;
    block-size: 0;
    overflow: clip;
    transition:
      block-size 0.45s var(--ease-out-quart),
      opacity 0.3s ease,
      content-visibility 0.45s allow-discrete;
  }
  details.rb-faq[open]::details-content {
    opacity: 1;
    block-size: auto;
  }
</style>
